</form><html xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:math="java.lang.Math" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns:xs="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" xmlns:fo="http://www.w3.org/1999/XSL/Format" xmlns:fn="http://www.w3.org/2005/02/xpath-functions" xmlns:xdt="http://www.w3.org/2005/02/xpath-datatypes" xmlns:caml="http://lc.ca.gov/legalservices/schemas/caml.1#" xmlns:xhtml="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><head><title>SCR127:v97#DOCUMENT</title><meta name="dc:identifier" content="SCR127"/><meta name="dc:title" content="SCR &#xA;              127-&#xA;                CHAPTERED&#xA;              "/><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html;charset=utf-8"/></head><body><span class="hidden"><h2>Bill Start</h2></span><div id="bill_all" align="justify"><div id="about"><br clear="all"/><div width="100%" style="text-align:center;"><div id="bill_num_title_chap"><span style="text-align:center;font-weight:bold;font-size:1.1em;font-family:'Times New Roman'; "><b>
                Senate Concurrent Resolution
              
                        No. 127</b></span></div><div style="text-align:center;padding-top: 1.0em;padding-bottom: 1.2em;" id="chap_num_title_chap"><span style="font-size:1.4em;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;">
                      CHAPTER 26</span></div></div><br clear="all"/><div id="title"><span style="font-weight:normal;font-size:0.9em;"> Relative to Multifaith Heritage Month.</span></div><br clear="all"/><div align="center">
                  
                  [<span style="  font-size: 1.3em">
                Filed with
              </span><span style="  font-size: 1.3em">
                Secretary of State
              </span> <span style="font-size: 13pt">April 17, 2026.
                      </span>]
                </div><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><h2>LEGISLATIVE COUNSEL'S DIGEST</h2></div><br/><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0"><span id="subject">SCR 127, Allen.
                          Multifaith Heritage Month.</span></div><div><span id="digesttext"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">This measure would designate the month of December each year as Multifaith Heritage Month, and would encourage residents of California to join in fostering a community grounded in mutual respect, understanding, and harmony among diverse faiths and cultures.</div></span></div><span class="hidden"><h2>Digest Key</h2></span><span id="fiscalcommittee">
      Fiscal Committee:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">NO</span>  </span></div><hr/><span class="hidden"><h2>Bill Text</h2></span><span class="Resolution" title="source: /caml:MeasureDoc/caml:Resolution&#xA;    "><span class="Whereas" id="id_4EAA2A8C-BA9E-4338-B35E-F043328F2198"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, The State of California is recognized as a beacon of multifaith harmony where diverse faith traditions increasingly weave into the fabric of everyday life, enriching the social, cultural, and spiritual life of the community; and </div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_5042278D-2F72-4968-A2B1-40DAAD4C29A5"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, The residents of California celebrate the vibrant tapestry of beliefs that characterize our multifaith community, fostering unity, understanding, and open dialogue among people of different faiths and backgrounds; and </div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_67E8F0B9-31C5-487E-BE69-A9AE15082140"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, By embracing a wide array of faiths and cultures, California cultivates an environment that values diversity, promotes a sense of belonging for all individuals, and strengthens the country’s distinctive identity as a place of inclusion and respect; and </div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_0C5C82B0-6F71-42B0-A808-52E9950AB6F0"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, The MultiFaith Initiative is a statewide organization whose mission is to welcome, stand with, and celebrate the major faith and spiritual traditions in our communities, promoting understanding, respect, and cooperative activities while partnering with other organizations to realize our common values and goals; and </div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_A1160DD6-5B23-4EFA-8E68-F0B361F4DA2B"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, In alignment with the principles of peace, justice, and equity, the MultiFaith Initiative encourages the community to pledge itself as a multifaith state and commit to nonviolence, access to essential resources such as education, health care, security, and technology, and treating all individuals with fairness, compassion, and respect; and </div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_91B47DD9-93E9-41D0-B974-4227EE191D96"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, The residents and leadership of California aspire to uphold truth, rationality, and ethical decisionmaking in public and private life and act with justice and compassion while celebrating the diversity of faiths, cultures, and lifestyles that enrich the lives of all California residents; now, therefore, be it</div></span><span class="Resolved" id="id_83E99E18-4ACB-43B4-83D6-3BA6A6C0A0BA"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Resolved by the Senate of the State of California, the Assembly thereof concurring, That the State of California designates the month of December each year as Multifaith Heritage Month and encourages all residents to join in fostering a community grounded in mutual respect, understanding, and harmony among diverse faiths and cultures. </div></span></span></div></body></html>
